stylometry: One reason why integer programming models are difficult is because solver doesn't like IF statements which these models use but more importantly, integer programming models are very complex problems. They have to search numerous possiblilities which takes a very long time to do. For this reason, branch and bound is used. Branch and bound starts looking down one path but once it determines that it is not the best outcome, then is stops looking down that path and moves on to the next one. The IF function returns an output if the function is evaluated to be true or it returns another output if the function is evaluated to be false.
